GGiraph

This is a worksheet for voronoi plots produced in ggiraph. There are 2 different types; a voronoi and a point.

They’re applied to both the total clinic list, and each clinic type.

Libraries

library(ggiraph)
library(tidyverse)
library(openprescribingR)
library(sf)

Functions

bbox_polygon <- function(x) {
  bb <- sf::st_bbox(x)
  p <- matrix(
    c(bb["xmin"], bb["ymin"], 
      bb["xmin"], bb["ymax"],
      bb["xmax"], bb["ymax"], 
      bb["xmax"], bb["ymin"], 
      bb["xmin"], bb["ymin"]),
    ncol = 2, byrow = T
  )
  sf::st_polygon(list(p))
}

voronoifun <- function(nc_centroids) {
box <- st_sfc(bbox_polygon(nc_centroids))
v <- st_voronoi(st_union(nc_centroids), box)
rm(nc_centroids, box)
polygons <- st_intersection(st_cast(v), st_union(ccggeom)) %>%
  as_Spatial() %>%
  fortify()
}

geometryfun <- function(clinics) {
  st_as_sf(clinics, coords = c("Longitude", "Latitude"), crs = 4326, agr = "constant")
}

types <- unique(alldata$type)

  filter(type == types[5]) %>%

  filter(type == types[6]) %>%
  unique()

  filter(type == types[7]) %>%
  unique()

GPledUCCwED <- alldata[c(4,8,9,10)] %>%
  filter(type == types[8]) %>%
  unique()

  filter(type == types[9]) %>%
  unique()

clinics <- list(DE, ED, GPledUCCwED, IUCCAS, MIU, OOH, SpecED, UUH, WIC)
clinictitles <- c("DE", "ED", "GPledUCCwED", "IUCCAS", "MIU", "OOH", "SpecED", "UUH", "WIC")

#clean up
rm(IUCCAS, SpecED, WIC, ED, MIU, OOH, UUH, GPledUCCwED, DE)

clinics <- lapply(clinics, geometryfun)
voronoiclinics <- lapply(clinics, voronoifun)

Plots

plots.plot1 =  ggplot() +
  geom_polygon_interactive(data = ukpolygon, aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group)) +
  geom_point_interactive(data = lat_long, aes(x = Longitude, y = Latitude, tooltip = Type), colour = "grey") +
  coord_sf(crs= 4326, datum = sf::st_crs(4326))
ggiraph(code = {print(plots.plot1)}, hover_css = "fill:red; fill-opacity:0.5;", width_svg = 17.07, height_svg = 13.46, width=1) %>%
